REACT FRONT-END SETUP GUIDE

1)	Prerequisites to Download:
•	Node.js and npm (Node Package Manager) has to be downloaded.
•	Raise Ticket to download Node.js.
•	Ensure that you have latest version of Node.js installed. This will include npm, which is used to manage packages.

2)	Setting Up React Project:
•	Use the command below in vs code terminal, to create a new React application:
npx create-react-app my-react-app
•	Replace my-react-app with your desired project name.

3)	Proxy and Network Settings:
•	Use the npm config command vs code terminal, to set up proxy:
npm config set https-proxy http://Windows Username@Windows Password@10.98.21.23:8080
npm config set proxy http:// Windows Username@Windows Password @10.98.21.23:8080

npm config set https-proxy http://dasan:W@lcom@18@10.98.21.23:8080
npm config set proxy http://dasan:W@lcom@18@10.98.21.23:8080

•	Replace Windows Username & Password with your Windows Username & Password.
•	Contact Naveen for more information.

4)	Common Dependencies to consider:
•	React Router for client-side navigation(in vs code terminal):
npm install react-router-dom
•	Axios for HTTP requests(in vs code terminal):
npm install axios
Verify the Installation
  npm list react
  npm list react-dom

Once above steps are done, perform below steps manually.

>mkdir src\\components
src\components\VoiceAgent.jsx
src\components\RecordButton.jsx
src\components\RecordButton.jsx

voice-project-status/
