5)	AG Grid and Licensing:
•	AG Grid : This library is used for advanced data tables and grid functionality.
•	License Key is needed.
•	Contact Naveen for AG Grid and License Key.

6)	CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing):
•	What is CORS : It is a security feature implemented by browsers to prevent unauthorized access to resources on a different domain.
•	Why is it Important : If your React app is running on http://localhost:3000 and your API server is on http://localhost:5000 , CORS needs to be configured on the server to allow the frontend to make API requests.
•	Install the CORS package(in vs code terminal):
npm install cors
•	Add it to server code:
app = Flask(__name__)
cors(app)

7)	Useful Commands:
•	Installing Dependencies(in vs code terminal):
npm install [package-name]
•	Running Tests (in vs code terminal):
npm test
•	Running Development Server in vs code terminal(To Start React application):
npm start
•	Building for Production(in vs code terminal):
npm run build 
